# App update publish workflow

When shipping app changes that users should receive via Settings → Check for updates:

1. Bump `versionCode` and `versionName` in `app/build.gradle.kts`.
2. Run `.\gradlew assembleRelease` (copies `docs/FamilyBank.apk` and regenerates `docs/app-update.json`).
3. Commit the app changes plus `docs/FamilyBank.apk` and `docs/app-update.json`.
4. Push to `origin/main` so GitHub Pages serves the new manifest and APK.

Do not leave update-related work uncommitted or unpushed unless the user explicitly asks to hold off.
